Fork created to allow MovementConstraint to take into account selection rotation


***** VERSION 2

This is a Version 2 release of ObjectHandles.  It was a rewrite from scratch with a completely different API.  If
you're upgrading from a 1.0 release, you may want to look for a download with a "1.0" version number such as: 
ObjectHandles-1.0.0015-src.zip   	 

Most of the examples and instructions on the website are still targetting version 1

***** SWCs

The easiest way to get started is to grab the appropriate .swc from the the deploy folder, copy that to the
libs folder of your project, and start using the classes.

***** Examples

Examples can be found in 
  ObjectHandles2Example.mxml  (A comprehensive set of examples)
  ObjectHandlesFlex4Example.mxml  (A specialized example showing how to use ObjectHandles in Flex 4)
Other example classes are in: com.roguedevelopment.objecthandles.examples

***** SUPPORT

For support, please see the google group at: http://groups.google.com/group/objecthandles

The group is the best place for support!

***** Using Object Handles?
Please tell us about projects using ObjectHandles, we love to see them.  We'd love to list it on our usage page
http://code.google.com/p/flex-object-handles/wiki/ObjectHandlesUsage

We've had over 75,000 downloads, but only know about a half dozen projects using ObjectHandles.  Please consider letting us 
know about yours, it really helps to keep us motivated.

***** DOWNLOADS

The latest version of this project can always be downloaded from: http://code.google.com/p/flex-object-handles/downloads/list


